name: Crispy Shiitake Wontons
description: Deep fried plant-based wontons filled with tofu, shiitake mushroom and seasonal vegetables. Served with sweet and sour sauce.

name: Nộm (Vietnamese Root Salad)
description: Vietnamese inspired fine-julienne seasonal root mix topped with pickled vegetable, fresh mint dressing and seasoned rice paper crisp.

name: Karaage (Japanese Fried Chicken)
description: Shoyu marinated, topped with teriyaki sauce, lemon aioli, nori and bonito flakes.

name: Mushroom Lentil Pâté
description: Packed in umami flavour, this herb infused plant-based pâté is served with house-made maple whole grain mustard, pickled onion and garlic crostini. GF-option served with fried rice paper.

name: Deep Fried Wontons
description: House-made pork and shrimp wontons. Served with sweet and sour sauce.

name: Thai Milk Tea Tiramisu
description: Creamy, rich, and bursting with a milk tea flavor. This modern Thai twist on the classic Italian dessert layered with sponge cake, light and airy mascarpone cream and a silky Thai tea crème anglaise.

name: Spicy Korean BBQ Pork
description: Thin sliced spicy pork belly served with Korean BBQ sauce, house-made kimchi, sesame oil, lettuce, seasonal vegetables and rice.

name: Tan Tan Noodle
description: Originated from the Sichuan region of China which combines spicy minced pork, slow-cooked chicken broth, pickled mustard greens and chili oil. Topped with crispy egg noodles.

name: Ochazuke
description: A seasonal twist on an iconic Japanese comfort food. Made with spiced winter squash purée, confit butternut squash and rice. Poured with a savoury green tea dashi broth.

name: Thai Red Curry
description: House-made spicy Thai red curry paste, coconut milk, seasonal vegetables, lemongrass and fresh herbs, served with rice.
